Class Prescription

java.lang.Object
medicalrecords.Prescription
public class Prescription extends Object
The Prescription class represents a medical prescription for a patient. It includes information about the medication, dosage, frequency, amount, instructions, and the status of the prescription.

  • Constructor Details

    • Prescription

      public Prescription(String medicationName, String dosage, String instructions, String frequency, int amount, int status)
      Constructs a Prescription object with the specified details.
      Parameters:
      medicationName - the name of the medication
      dosage - the dosage information (e.g., "500mg twice a day")
      instructions - any special instructions for taking the medication
      frequency - the frequency of administration (e.g., "2 times per day")
      amount - the number of units prescribed (e.g., 30 tablets)
      status - the status of the prescription (e.g., pending, prescribed, filled)

  • Method Details

    • fromCSV

      public static Prescription fromCSV(String csvString)
      Creates a Prescription object from a CSV string. The string should be formatted as "medicationName|dosage|frequency|amount|instructions|status".
      Parameters:
      csvString - the CSV string to parse
      Returns:
      a Prescription object created from the parsed CSV string
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the CSV format is invalid
